    "Influence Areas Details Education and public schools,\nCity budget and school funding,\nLong-term infrastructure planning (waste water plant),\nEconomic development and Tourism,\nHistoric and environmental preservation,\n“Community of Events” and family friendly environment,\nFree Lance Star=unreliable\n His GIS and data-analytics background means he responds well to quantitative, evidence-based arguments. Lead with maps, traffic modeling, and fiscal impact projections tied to schools and public services — the two issues he has staked his identity on. Frame data center tax revenue explicitly as what funds the school resources he has championed. Downtown business community and Small business growth\r\nQuality of life, Affordable housing, Workforce housing\r\nPedestrian safety and Reuse of existing spaces\r\nPublic schools and Teacher pay\r\nEnvironmental protection and Historic preservation\r\nSupport for vulnerable residents\r She is process-oriented, transparency-focused, and acutely attentive to community impact documentation. The winning argument for any new data center project is: robust public engagement, clear environmental performance standards, and a concrete mechanism tying revenue to affordable housing and sustainability (the two trust funds she has publicly called for).": "",
